sequenceDiagram
    participant Build as Konflux Build System
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator<br/>Platform Operator
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant User as User Browser
    participant NbCtrl as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Kubelet as kubelet
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>Envoy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>(JupyterLab / code-server / RStudio)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over Build,Registry: Flow 1: Workbench Image Deployment

    Build->>Registry: Push built images<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Service Account
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply kustomize manifests<br/>(Create ImageStreams)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStream annotations<br/>(opendatahub.io/notebook-image-name,<br/>notebook-software, python-dependencies)<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Notebook Session

    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC SSO
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    NbCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CR<br/>Create StatefulSet + kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Kubelet->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Pull secret

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: Active Notebook Session

    User->>Gateway: Access notebook<br/>POST /notebook/{ns}/{name}/lab<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC cookie
    Gateway->>RBAC: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    RBAC->>Notebook: Proxy to workbench<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>localhost/pod network<br/>Auth: None (pre-authenticated)
    Notebook-->>RBAC: Response (HTML/WebSocket)
    RBAC-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: Response

    Note over Notebook,Registry: Flow 4: Runtime Egress (User-Initiated)

    Notebook->>Registry: pip install (user packages)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Note right of Notebook: Also: Git repos (443/TCP),<br/>S3 storage (443/TCP),<br/>MongoDB (27017/TCP),<br/>ODBC sources (varies)
